52:47.000 --> 52:48.000
between colleagues at work,

52:49.000 --> 52:50.000
both within the organization

52:51.000 --> 52:52.000
and between them.

52:53.000 --> 52:54.000
As a rule,

52:55.000 --> 52:56.000
horizontal communications

52:57.000 --> 52:58.000
not only pursue the goal

52:59.000 --> 53:00.000
of informing someone about something,

53:01.000 --> 53:02.000
but also ask for coordination of actions.

53:03.000 --> 53:04.000
Horizontal communications

53:05.000 --> 53:06.000
are divided into three categories.

53:07.000 --> 53:08.000
The first one

53:09.000 --> 53:10.000
is the solution of problems within departments.

53:11.000 --> 53:12.000
Such messages, as a rule,

53:13.000 --> 53:14.000
are associated with the execution of tasks.

53:15.000 --> 53:16.000
For example,

53:17.000 --> 53:18.000
Svetlana,

53:19.000 --> 53:20.000
can you help us fill in the list

53:21.000 --> 53:22.000
of representative expenses?

53:23.000 --> 53:24.000
The second type of message

53:25.000 --> 53:26.000
is coordination of work in departments.

53:27.000 --> 53:28.000
These are messages

53:29.000 --> 53:30.000
that departments exchange

53:31.000 --> 53:32.000
to fulfill

53:33.000 --> 53:34.000
joint projects or common tasks.

53:35.000 --> 53:36.000
For example,

53:37.000 --> 53:38.000
Ivan, please contact the marketing and production department

53:39.000 --> 53:40.000
and arrange a meeting.

53:41.000 --> 53:42.000
We need to discuss some issues.

53:43.000 --> 53:44.000
The next category of messages

53:45.000 --> 53:46.000
is initiatives of changes and improvements.

53:47.000 --> 53:48.000
Such messages

53:49.000 --> 53:50.000
are exchanged by teams and departments

53:51.000 --> 53:52.000
in an attempt to change,

53:53.000 --> 53:54.000
improve or develop the organization.

53:55.000 --> 53:56.000
For example,

53:57.000 --> 53:58.000
