58:07.000 --> 58:08.000
and each member of the team

58:09.000 --> 58:10.000
has the opportunity to actively participate

58:11.000 --> 58:12.000
in making decisions.

58:13.000 --> 58:14.000
The accuracy of the decision changes

58:15.000 --> 58:16.000
along with the level of difficulty of the problems.

58:17.000 --> 58:18.000
Centralized networks

58:19.000 --> 58:20.000
make fewer mistakes

58:21.000 --> 58:22.000
in simple tasks,

58:23.000 --> 58:24.000
but become less effective

58:25.000 --> 58:26.000
in solving complex problems.

58:27.000 --> 58:28.000
In this way,

58:29.000 --> 58:30.000
it is fair to conclude

58:31.000 --> 58:32.000
that in conditions of

58:33.000 --> 58:34.000
tough global competition,

58:35.000 --> 58:36.000
teams are used

58:37.000 --> 58:38.000
to solve complex problems.

58:39.000 --> 58:40.000
If the task set

58:41.000 --> 58:42.000
before the team

58:43.000 --> 58:44.000
is really difficult,

58:45.000 --> 58:46.000
all its members

58:47.000 --> 58:48.000
should have access to information,

58:49.000 --> 58:50.000
i.e. a decentralized structure

58:51.000 --> 58:52.000
in which the information

58:53.000 --> 58:54.000
and communication

58:55.000 --> 58:56.000
that fulfills routine tasks

58:57.000 --> 58:58.000
spend much less time

58:59.000 --> 59:00.000
on processing the information,

59:01.000 --> 59:02.000
which means that a more adequate

59:03.000 --> 59:04.000
centralized structure is presented.

59:05.000 --> 59:06.000
This organization assumes

59:07.000 --> 59:08.000
that the data is sent

59:09.000 --> 59:10.000
to the leader

59:11.000 --> 59:12.000
who makes the decisions,

59:13.000 --> 59:14.000
and the members

59:15.000 --> 59:16.000
have free time

59:17.000 --> 59:18.000
to perform ordinary tasks.

59:19.000 --> 59:20.000
Informal communication channels

59:21.000 --> 59:22.000
are not connected

59:23.000 --> 59:24.000
with legalized formal channels

59:25.000 --> 59:26.000
but are connected

59:27.000 --> 59:28.000
with the structure of the organization.

59:29.000 --> 59:30.000
Informal communication

59:31.000 --> 59:32.000
coexists with formal communication,

59:33.000 --> 59:34.000
but does not depend on the hierarchy level

59:35.000 --> 59:36.000
and connects all employees in the organization.

59:37.000 --> 59:38.000
As a rule,

59:39.000 --> 59:40.000
there are two types of informal channels

59:41.000 --> 59:42.000
in organizations

59:43.000 --> 59:44.000
– walking management

59:45.000 --> 59:46.000
and secret telegraph.

59:47.000 --> 59:48.000
Walking management,

59:49.000 --> 59:50.000
based on the exits to the people,

59:51.000 --> 59:52.000
became widely known

59:53.000 --> 59:54.000
thanks to the popular bestseller

59:55.000 --> 59:56.000
about the leaders

59:57.000 --> 59:58.000
who prefer to receive information

59:59.000 --> 01:00:00.000
about the company's activities

01:00:01.000 --> 01:00:02.000
directly from conversations

01:00:03.000 --> 01:00:04.000
with employees.

01:00:05.000 --> 01:00:06.000
This method of communication

01:00:07.000 --> 01:00:08.000
can be used by managers of all levels.

01:00:09.000 --> 01:00:10.000
For example,

01:00:11.000 --> 01:00:12.000
the president of the company ARCA

01:00:13.000 --> 01:00:14.000
had a habit of visiting

01:00:15.000 --> 01:00:16.000
the regional department of the company,

01:00:17.000 --> 01:00:18.000
and instead of appointing

01:00:19.000 --> 01:00:20.000
an official meeting

01:00:21.000 --> 01:00:22.000
with the director of the department,

01:00:23.000 --> 01:00:24.000
he came incognito

01:00:25.000 --> 01:00:26.000
and was not able to meet

01:00:27.000 --> 01:00:28.000
the director of the department.

01:00:29.000 --> 01:00:30.000
In the case of walking management,

01:00:31.000 --> 01:00:32.000
it helps to strengthen

01:00:33.000 --> 01:00:34.000
both rising and falling communications.

01:00:35.000 --> 01:00:36.000
Managers have the opportunity

01:00:37.000 --> 01:00:38.000
to convey their ideas and values

01:00:39.000 --> 01:00:40.000
to employees

01:00:41.000 --> 01:00:42.000
and hear about the problems

01:00:43.000 --> 01:00:44.000
of worrying employees.

01:00:45.000 --> 01:00:46.000
A manager unable to manage

01:00:47.000 --> 01:00:48.000
the walking management

01:00:49.000 --> 01:00:50.000
feels his alienation,

01:00:51.000 --> 01:00:52.000
some kind of detachment

01:00:53.000 --> 01:00:54.000
and isolation from his subordinates.

01:00:55.000 --> 01:00:56.000
The secret telegraph

01:00:57.000 --> 01:00:58.000
exists always and everywhere.

01:00:59.000 --> 01:01:00.000
If the formal channels of communication

01:01:01.000 --> 01:01:02.000
in organizations are closed,

01:01:03.000 --> 01:01:04.000
it acquires the character

01:01:05.000 --> 01:01:06.000
of a dominating principle of communication.

01:01:07.000 --> 01:01:08.000
But in this case,

01:01:09.000 --> 01:01:10.000
it is undoubtedly useful

01:01:11.000 --> 01:01:12.000
because information is spread

01:01:13.000 --> 01:01:14.000
through it,

01:01:15.000 --> 01:01:16.000
which contributes

01:01:17.000 --> 01:01:18.000
to a more adequate perception of the situation.

01:01:19.000 --> 01:01:20.000
Rumors allow employees

01:01:21.000 --> 01:01:22.000
to fill the information vacuum

01:01:23.000 --> 01:01:24.000
and to be able to

01:01:25.000 --> 01:01:26.000
clarify various decisions of management.

01:01:27.000 --> 01:01:28.000
The telegraph is activated

01:01:29.000 --> 01:01:30.000
when there are changes in the company,

01:01:31.000 --> 01:01:32.000
when there is anxiety

01:01:33.000 --> 01:01:34.000
or when the economic situation is worsening.

01:01:35.000 --> 01:01:36.000
Studies show

01:01:37.000 --> 01:01:38.000
that the effectiveness of the secret telegraph

01:01:39.000 --> 01:01:40.000
depends primarily

01:01:41.000 --> 01:01:42.000
on several people.

01:01:43.000 --> 01:01:44.000
Slide 27 presents

01:01:45.000 --> 01:01:46.000
two of its most common schemes.

01:01:47.000 --> 01:01:48.000
In a simple chain,

01:01:49.000 --> 01:01:50.000
one person reports

01:01:51.000 --> 01:01:52.000
any new information

01:01:52.000 --> 01:01:53.000
to many others,

01:01:54.000 --> 01:01:55.000
and in a cluster chain

01:01:56.000 --> 01:01:57.000
information is transmitted

01:01:58.000 --> 01:01:59.000
by several individuals.

01:02:00.000 --> 01:02:01.000
The smaller the number of transfer links,

01:02:02.000 --> 01:02:03.000
the more accurate the information.

01:02:04.000 --> 01:02:05.000
With their increase,

01:02:06.000 --> 01:02:07.000
the secret telegraph

01:02:08.000 --> 01:02:09.000
turns into a spoiled phone.

01:02:10.000 --> 01:02:11.000
What is surprising is that

01:02:12.000 --> 01:02:13.000
the information transmitted

01:02:14.000 --> 01:02:15.000
by the secret telegraph

01:02:16.000 --> 01:02:17.000
differs in reliability

01:02:18.000 --> 01:02:19.000
and is usually dedicated

01:02:20.000 --> 01:02:21.000
to organizational problems.

01:02:22.000 --> 01:02:23.000
The information transmitted

01:02:24.000 --> 01:02:25.000
is somehow connected

01:02:26.000 --> 01:02:27.000
with the business

01:02:28.000 --> 01:02:29.000
and has nothing in common with the rumors.

01:02:30.000 --> 01:02:31.000
Moreover,

01:02:32.000 --> 01:02:34.000
up to 90% of the data is confirmed.

01:02:35.000 --> 01:02:36.000
Many managers

01:02:37.000 --> 01:02:38.000
are negatively related to the secret telegraph

01:02:39.000 --> 01:02:40.000
and would be happy to get rid of it.

01:02:41.000 --> 01:02:42.000
However, it should be borne in mind

01:02:43.000 --> 01:02:44.000
that almost 5 out of 6

01:02:45.000 --> 01:02:46.000
important messages

01:02:47.000 --> 01:02:48.000
are distributed to some extent

01:02:49.000 --> 01:02:50.000
by means of the secret telegraph

01:02:50.000 --> 01:02:51.000
via official channels.

01:02:52.000 --> 01:02:53.000
A survey of 22,000 shift workers

01:02:54.000 --> 01:02:55.000
from various industries

01:02:56.000 --> 01:02:57.000
showed that

01:02:58.000 --> 01:02:59.000
55% of them

01:03:00.000 --> 01:03:01.000
receive the bulk of information

01:03:02.000 --> 01:03:03.000
through the secret telegraph.

01:03:04.000 --> 01:03:05.000
The most remote managers

01:03:06.000 --> 01:03:07.000
are well versed

01:03:08.000 --> 01:03:09.000
in the subtleties

01:03:10.000 --> 01:03:11.000
of this means of communication.

01:03:12.000 --> 01:03:13.000
They know who is connected with whom

01:03:14.000 --> 01:03:15.000
and who of the workers

01:03:16.000 --> 01:03:17.000
plays a leading role

01:03:18.000 --> 01:03:19.000
in the informal distribution

01:03:20.000 --> 01:03:21.000
of information.

01:03:22.000 --> 01:03:23.000
In all cases,

01:03:24.000 --> 01:03:25.000
especially in crisis moments,

01:03:26.000 --> 01:03:27.000
it is necessary to manage communications

01:03:28.000 --> 01:03:29.000
wisely so that the secret telegraph

01:03:30.000 --> 01:03:31.000
does not become the only source of information.

01:03:32.000 --> 01:03:33.000
Communication barriers of the organization

01:03:34.000 --> 01:03:35.000
Although communication in organizations

01:03:36.000 --> 01:03:37.000
often has an interpersonal nature,

01:03:38.000 --> 01:03:39.000
however,

01:03:40.000 --> 01:03:41.000
not always the problems of their organization

01:03:42.000 --> 01:03:43.000
are exhausted by interpersonal barriers.

01:03:44.000 --> 01:03:45.000
Often,

01:03:46.000 --> 01:03:47.000
on the path of effective communication

01:03:48.000 --> 01:03:49.000
and, accordingly,

01:03:50.000 --> 01:03:51.000
on the path of successful work of the organization

01:03:52.000 --> 01:03:53.000
there are specific barriers

01:03:54.000 --> 01:03:55.000
associated with various problems

01:03:56.000 --> 01:03:57.000
of the organization as a whole.

01:03:58.000 --> 01:03:59.000
These organizational barriers

01:04:00.000 --> 01:04:01.000
in communications

01:04:02.000 --> 01:04:03.000
deserve special attention

01:04:04.000 --> 01:04:05.000
because their nature

01:04:06.000 --> 01:04:07.000
is not associated with the specifics

01:04:08.000 --> 01:04:09.000
of the individual or group behavior of people,

01:04:10.000 --> 01:04:11.000
but with the problems of the organization itself.

01:04:12.000 --> 01:04:13.000
When information moves

01:04:14.000 --> 01:04:15.000
up and down inside the organization,

01:04:16.000 --> 01:04:17.000
the meaning of the message

01:04:18.000 --> 01:04:19.000
can be distorted.

01:04:20.000 --> 01:04:21.000
This can be due to a number of reasons.

01:04:22.000 --> 01:04:23.000
Messages can be distorted

01:04:24.000 --> 01:04:25.000
unintentionally due to difficulties

01:04:26.000 --> 01:04:27.000
in interpersonal contacts.

01:04:28.000 --> 01:04:29.000
However, other factors

01:04:30.000 --> 01:04:31.000
play a significant role

01:04:32.000 --> 01:04:33.000
in the appearance of distortions.

01:04:34.000 --> 01:04:35.000
Firstly,

01:04:36.000 --> 01:04:37.000
it is possible that the information

01:04:38.000 --> 01:04:39.000
is deliberately distorted by the source.

01:04:40.000 --> 01:04:41.000
Such distortion can take place,

01:04:42.000 --> 01:04:43.000
for example,

01:04:44.000 --> 01:04:45.000
when the message serves

01:04:46.000 --> 01:04:47.000
to assess the activity of the source

01:04:48.000 --> 01:04:49.000
and it is modified

01:04:50.000 --> 01:04:51.000
in accordance with the needs

01:04:52.000 --> 01:04:53.000
of the source.

01:04:54.000 --> 01:04:55.000
Secondly,

01:04:56.000 --> 01:04:57.000
another important problem

01:04:58.000 --> 01:04:59.000
is associated with the so-called

01:05:00.000 --> 01:05:01.000
filtering of information.

01:05:02.000 --> 01:05:03.000
Filtering is a process

01:05:04.000 --> 01:05:05.000
of losing part of the message

01:05:06.000 --> 01:05:07.000
due to inevitable losses

01:05:08.000 --> 01:05:09.000
of any nature

01:05:10.000 --> 01:05:11.000
when moving up or down

01:05:12.000 --> 01:05:13.000
the levels of the management hierarchy

01:05:14.000 --> 01:05:15.000
or within one level of the organization

01:05:16.000 --> 01:05:17.000
from one employee

01:05:18.000 --> 01:05:19.000
to another employee.

01:05:20.000 --> 01:05:21.000
The loss of a message

01:05:22.000 --> 01:05:23.000
when moving up

01:05:24.000 --> 01:05:25.000
the levels of the management hierarchy,

01:05:26.000 --> 01:05:27.000
when selecting information,

01:05:28.000 --> 01:05:29.000
when distributing it

01:05:30.000 --> 01:05:31.000
among different recipients,

01:05:32.000 --> 01:05:33.000
when purposefully

01:05:34.000 --> 01:05:35.000
cutting off the information

01:05:36.000 --> 01:05:37.000
from the general management

01:05:38.000 --> 01:05:39.000
and simplifying the message

01:05:40.000 --> 01:05:41.000
in the event of the transmission

01:05:42.000 --> 01:05:43.000
of specific instructions to the subordinates.

01:05:44.000 --> 01:05:45.000
The managers who transmit the message

01:05:46.000 --> 01:05:47.000
and determine what to transmit

01:05:47.000 --> 01:05:48.000
come from the desire

01:05:49.000 --> 01:05:50.000
to overcome all possible obstacles

01:05:51.000 --> 01:05:52.000
in interpersonal contacts

01:05:53.000 --> 01:05:54.000
from their own assessment

01:05:55.000 --> 01:05:56.000
of the importance and utility

01:05:57.000 --> 01:05:58.000
of a particular piece of information.

01:05:59.000 --> 01:06:00.000
This moment pushes them

01:06:01.000 --> 01:06:02.000
to filter them

01:06:03.000 --> 01:06:04.000
and to emphasize other messages.

01:06:05.000 --> 01:06:06.000
Such selection may be the reason

01:06:07.000 --> 01:06:08.000
for not getting important information

01:06:09.000 --> 01:06:10.000
to another sector of the organization

01:06:11.000 --> 01:06:12.000
or for getting information

01:06:13.000 --> 01:06:14.000
with a significant distortion of meaning.

01:06:14.000 --> 01:06:15.000
For example,

01:06:16.000 --> 01:06:17.000
one study showed

01:06:18.000 --> 01:06:19.000
that only 63% of the information

01:06:20.000 --> 01:06:21.000
sent by the Board of Directors

01:06:22.000 --> 01:06:23.000
reached the Vice-Presidents,

01:06:24.000 --> 01:06:25.000
40% reached the managers

01:06:26.000 --> 01:06:27.000
and only 20% reached the employees.

01:06:28.000 --> 01:06:29.000
There may be other reasons

01:06:30.000 --> 01:06:31.000
for filtering the information.

01:06:32.000 --> 01:06:33.000
For example,

01:06:34.000 --> 01:06:35.000
messages sent up

01:06:36.000 --> 01:06:37.000
the levels of the management hierarchy

01:06:38.000 --> 01:06:39.000
may be distorted

01:06:40.000 --> 01:06:41.000
due to the tendency

01:06:42.000 --> 01:06:43.000
to provide the management

01:06:44.000 --> 01:06:45.000
with the opportunity

01:06:46.000 --> 01:06:47.000
to receive only positive information.

01:06:48.000 --> 01:06:49.000
This may lead to the fact

01:06:50.000 --> 01:06:51.000
that the subordinate

01:06:52.000 --> 01:06:53.000
does not inform the manager

01:06:54.000 --> 01:06:55.000
about a potential or existing problem

01:06:56.000 --> 01:06:57.000
because he does not want to

01:06:58.000 --> 01:06:59.000
tell the boss bad news.

01:07:00.000 --> 01:07:01.000
Since the subordinates often want

01:07:02.000 --> 01:07:03.000
to receive approval from the manager,

01:07:04.000 --> 01:07:05.000
they can only tell him

01:07:06.000 --> 01:07:07.000
what he wants to hear.

01:07:08.000 --> 01:07:09.000
Studies show

01:07:10.000 --> 01:07:11.000
that such status differences

01:07:12.000 --> 01:07:13.000
are strongly reflected

01:07:14.000 --> 01:07:15.000
in the way

01:07:16.000 --> 01:07:17.000
the management

01:07:18.000 --> 01:07:19.000
communicates the information.

01:07:20.000 --> 01:07:21.000
Among other reasons

01:07:22.000 --> 01:07:23.000
that prevent the employees

01:07:24.000 --> 01:07:25.000
from conveying the information

01:07:26.000 --> 01:07:27.000
may be fear of punishment

01:07:28.000 --> 01:07:29.000
and a sense of uselessness of their work.

01:07:30.000 --> 01:07:31.000
Another important reason

01:07:32.000 --> 01:07:33.000
why the content of the message

01:07:34.000 --> 01:07:35.000
may not reach the recipient

01:07:36.000 --> 01:07:37.000
is overloading the recipient

01:07:38.000 --> 01:07:39.000
with other incoming messages

01:07:40.000 --> 01:07:41.000
or his discontent

01:07:42.000 --> 01:07:43.000
with the subject of the message.

01:07:44.000 --> 01:07:45.000
The message

01:07:46.000 --> 01:07:47.000
may not reach the recipient.

01:07:48.000 --> 01:07:49.000
Organizations with complex

01:07:50.000 --> 01:07:51.000
multi-level structures

01:07:52.000 --> 01:07:53.000
may face other problems.

01:07:54.000 --> 01:07:55.000
The organizations' subordinates

01:07:56.000 --> 01:07:57.000
are themselves organizations

01:07:58.000 --> 01:07:59.000
and, consequently,

01:08:00.000 --> 01:08:01.000
they inevitably have their own goals.

01:08:02.000 --> 01:08:03.000
Therefore, if the organization's structure

01:08:04.000 --> 01:08:05.000
and motivation system

01:08:06.000 --> 01:08:07.000
are built in a bad way,

01:08:08.000 --> 01:08:09.000
the subordinates' goals

01:08:10.000 --> 01:08:11.000
may contradict

01:08:12.000 --> 01:08:13.000
the organization's common goals

01:08:14.000 --> 01:08:15.000
and the organization's goals.

01:08:16.000 --> 01:08:17.000
The higher the level of the organization's structure,

01:08:18.000 --> 01:08:19.000
the greater the probability

01:08:20.000 --> 01:08:21.000
of significant contradictions.

01:08:22.000 --> 01:08:23.000
To overcome the obstacles

01:08:24.000 --> 01:08:25.000
both in verbal and in written communication,

01:08:26.000 --> 01:08:27.000
the 5C communication system

01:08:28.000 --> 01:08:29.000
has been adopted.

01:08:30.000 --> 01:08:31.000
First of all,

01:08:32.000 --> 01:08:33.000
clarity.

01:08:34.000 --> 01:08:35.000
The message and information

01:08:36.000 --> 01:08:37.000
should be as clear

01:08:38.000 --> 01:08:39.000
as possible.

01:08:40.000 --> 01:08:41.000
Often insufficient clarity

01:08:41.000 --> 01:08:42.000
is caused by an attempt

01:08:43.000 --> 01:08:44.000
to express too many thoughts

01:08:45.000 --> 01:08:46.000
with one sentence.

01:08:47.000 --> 01:08:48.000
The second is completeness.

01:08:49.000 --> 01:08:50.000
Simplification of information

01:08:51.000 --> 01:08:52.000
may lead to its incompleteness.

01:08:53.000 --> 01:08:54.000
Some information

01:08:55.000 --> 01:08:56.000
may be more harmful

01:08:57.000 --> 01:08:58.000
than its complete absence.

01:08:59.000 --> 01:09:00.000
The next is correctness.

01:09:01.000 --> 01:09:02.000
In the case of long,

01:09:03.000 --> 01:09:04.000
unconnected messages,

01:09:05.000 --> 01:09:06.000
the problem is rarely associated

01:09:07.000 --> 01:09:08.000
with the excess of the topic.

01:09:09.000 --> 01:09:10.000
Much more often,

01:09:11.000 --> 01:09:12.000
the problem is with the specific message

01:09:13.000 --> 01:09:14.000
that the person wants to convey.

01:09:15.000 --> 01:09:16.000
The next is concreteness.

01:09:17.000 --> 01:09:18.000
Usually, communicators resort

01:09:19.000 --> 01:09:20.000
to abstractions and generalizations

01:09:21.000 --> 01:09:22.000
when they are not at all suitable

01:09:23.000 --> 01:09:24.000
for real, concrete facts.

01:09:25.000 --> 01:09:26.000
Abstraction is, of course,

01:09:27.000 --> 01:09:28.000
a value when we deal

01:09:29.000 --> 01:09:30.000
with abstract things.

01:09:31.000 --> 01:09:32.000
However, we waste precious time

01:09:33.000 --> 01:09:34.000
and abilities

01:09:35.000 --> 01:09:36.000
when we squeeze real things

01:09:37.000 --> 01:09:38.000
into abstract or non-concrete formulations.

01:09:39.000 --> 01:09:40.000
The choice of a specific terminology

01:09:41.000 --> 01:09:42.000
becomes more and more important

01:09:43.000 --> 01:09:44.000
as the business is globalized.

01:09:45.000 --> 01:09:46.000
A term used in one culture

01:09:47.000 --> 01:09:48.000
may have a completely opposite meaning

01:09:49.000 --> 01:09:50.000
in another.

01:09:51.000 --> 01:09:52.000
And finally, the last is correctness.

01:09:53.000 --> 01:09:54.000
It is completely useless

01:09:55.000 --> 01:09:56.000
to use communication techniques

01:09:57.000 --> 01:09:58.000
without any fault

01:09:59.000 --> 01:10:00.000
if the message you send is incorrect.

01:10:01.000 --> 01:10:02.000
Management should create

01:10:03.000 --> 01:10:04.000
such an organizational structure

01:10:05.000 --> 01:10:06.000
that will stimulate

01:10:07.000 --> 01:10:08.000
positive and effective communication,

01:10:09.000 --> 01:10:10.000
which requires both individual skills

01:10:11.000 --> 01:10:12.000
and organizational actions.

01:10:13.000 --> 01:10:14.000
First,

01:10:15.000 --> 01:10:16.000
the atmosphere of trust and openness

01:10:17.000 --> 01:10:18.000
in the organization

01:10:19.000 --> 01:10:20.000
encourages employees

01:10:21.000 --> 01:10:22.000
to have honest communication with each other.

01:10:23.000 --> 01:10:24.000
Then employees painlessly

01:10:25.000 --> 01:10:26.000
convey both good

01:10:27.000 --> 01:10:28.000
and bad news.

01:10:29.000 --> 01:10:30.000
To create such an atmosphere of trust

01:10:31.000 --> 01:10:32.000
and dialogue,

01:10:33.000 --> 01:10:34.000
it is necessary to make an effort

01:10:35.000 --> 01:10:36.000
to develop interpersonal

01:10:37.000 --> 01:10:38.000
quality of the employees.

01:10:39.000 --> 01:10:40.000
Secondly, managers must

01:10:41.000 --> 01:10:42.000
have formal communication channels

01:10:43.000 --> 01:10:44.000
in all areas.

01:10:45.000 --> 01:10:46.000
Thirdly, managers must

01:10:47.000 --> 01:10:48.000
stimulate simultaneous use

01:10:49.000 --> 01:10:50.000
of multiple communication channels

01:10:51.000 --> 01:10:52.000
both formal and informal.

01:10:53.000 --> 01:10:54.000
The number of such multiple channels

01:10:55.000 --> 01:10:56.000
includes written directives,

01:10:57.000 --> 01:10:58.000
face-to-face discussions,

01:10:59.000 --> 01:11:00.000
public appearances and secret telegraph.

01:11:01.000 --> 01:11:02.000
For example, at General Motors factories

01:11:03.000 --> 01:11:04.000
a newspaper is published every month.

01:11:05.000 --> 01:11:06.000
Managers regularly hold meetings

01:11:07.000 --> 01:11:08.000
with the company's employees

01:11:09.000 --> 01:11:10.000
to transmit news

01:11:11.000 --> 01:11:12.000
and to use electronic displays

01:11:13.000 --> 01:11:14.000
in the cafeteria.

01:11:15.000 --> 01:11:16.000
Sending messages

01:11:17.000 --> 01:11:18.000
through multiple channels

01:11:19.000 --> 01:11:20.000
simultaneously increases the chances

01:11:21.000 --> 01:11:22.000
that they will be received

01:11:23.000 --> 01:11:24.000
and correctly understood.

01:11:25.000 --> 01:11:26.000
Fourthly, the organization's structure

01:11:27.000 --> 01:11:28.000
must meet the needs of communication.

01:11:29.000 --> 01:11:30.000
If the organization has a shortage

01:11:31.000 --> 01:11:32.000
of horizontal communication channels,

01:11:33.000 --> 01:11:34.000
and teams can be created in it,

01:11:35.000 --> 01:11:36.000
specialized groups,

01:11:37.000 --> 01:11:38.000
managers' positions

01:11:38.000 --> 01:11:39.000
and matrix structures

01:11:40.000 --> 01:11:41.000
must be introduced.

01:11:42.000 --> 01:11:43.000
The organization's structure

01:11:44.000 --> 01:11:45.000
must reflect the needs

01:11:46.000 --> 01:11:47.000
of the information.

01:11:48.000 --> 01:11:49.000
If a department or team

01:11:50.000 --> 01:11:51.000
performs complex,

01:11:52.000 --> 01:11:53.000
non-standard tasks,

01:11:54.000 --> 01:11:55.000
a decentralized structure

01:11:56.000 --> 01:11:57.000
is necessary,

01:11:58.000 --> 01:11:59.000
which allows to intensify discussions

01:12:00.000 --> 01:12:01.000
and involve employees

01:12:02.000 --> 01:12:03.000
in the management process.

01:12:04.000 --> 01:12:05.000
Overcoming organizational

01:12:06.000 --> 01:12:07.000
and communication barriers

01:12:08.000 --> 01:12:09.000
is essential for the organization

01:12:10.000 --> 01:12:11.000
to have a high-quality

01:12:12.000 --> 01:12:13.000
and highly efficient

01:12:14.000 --> 01:12:15.000
communication technology.

01:12:16.000 --> 01:12:17.000
Communication and a high-quality

01:12:18.000 --> 01:12:20.000
workplace

01:12:21.000 --> 01:12:22.000
Progress in information technology

01:12:23.000 --> 01:12:24.000
allows organizations

01:12:25.000 --> 01:12:26.000
to distribute information

01:12:27.000 --> 01:12:28.000
faster than before,

01:12:29.000 --> 01:12:30.000
to have more access

01:12:31.000 --> 01:12:32.000
to the volume of information,

01:12:33.000 --> 01:12:34.000
to have a more efficient

01:12:35.000 --> 01:12:36.000
and reliable system

01:12:36.000 --> 01:12:37.000
to have a wider

01:12:38.000 --> 01:12:39.000
and direct access

01:12:40.000 --> 01:12:41.000
to this information,

01:12:42.000 --> 01:12:43.000
to encourage participation

01:12:44.000 --> 01:12:45.000
in the exchange of information

01:12:46.000 --> 01:12:47.000
and its use,

01:12:48.000 --> 01:12:49.000
to integrate systems and functions,

01:12:50.000 --> 01:12:51.000
and to use information

01:12:52.000 --> 01:12:53.000
for communication

01:12:54.000 --> 01:12:55.000
with the environment

01:12:56.000 --> 01:12:57.000
without any precedent.

01:12:58.000 --> 01:12:59.000
Negative sides

01:13:00.000 --> 01:13:01.000
of electronic communication

01:13:02.000 --> 01:13:03.000
must be realized.

01:13:04.000 --> 01:13:05.000
First, these technologies

01:13:06.000 --> 01:13:07.000
should interact with machines,

01:13:08.000 --> 01:13:09.000
not with each other.

01:13:10.000 --> 01:13:11.000
Electronics also eliminates

01:13:12.000 --> 01:13:13.000
the non-verbal component

01:13:14.000 --> 01:13:15.000
of communication,

01:13:16.000 --> 01:13:17.000
which can add additional context

01:13:18.000 --> 01:13:19.000
to the situation.

01:13:20.000 --> 01:13:21.000
Some people, for example,

01:13:22.000 --> 01:13:23.000
say that sending an e-mail

01:13:24.000 --> 01:13:25.000
is much easier to be harsh,

01:13:26.000 --> 01:13:27.000
overly critical and insensitive

01:13:28.000 --> 01:13:29.000
than in personal contact.

01:13:30.000 --> 01:13:31.000
In this sense,

01:13:32.000 --> 01:13:33.000
using computer communication

01:13:33.000 --> 01:13:34.000
can make people less restrained

01:13:35.000 --> 01:13:36.000
and more impatient

01:13:37.000 --> 01:13:38.000
in their statements.

01:13:39.000 --> 01:13:40.000
Another danger of new

01:13:41.000 --> 01:13:42.000
communication technologies

01:13:43.000 --> 01:13:44.000
is information overload.

01:13:45.000 --> 01:13:46.000
Individual users

01:13:47.000 --> 01:13:48.000
may have difficulties

01:13:49.000 --> 01:13:50.000
sorting useful and empty information.

01:13:51.000 --> 01:13:52.000
For example,

01:13:53.000 --> 01:13:54.000
giant IT company Intel

01:13:55.000 --> 01:13:56.000
has problems with e-mail.

01:13:57.000 --> 01:13:58.000
Employees of the company

01:13:59.000 --> 01:14:00.000
are forced to process

01:14:01.000 --> 01:14:02.000
more than 3 million e-mails a day.

01:14:03.000 --> 01:14:04.000
The messages

01:14:05.000 --> 01:14:06.000
on a certain topic

01:14:07.000 --> 01:14:08.000
are scattered

01:14:09.000 --> 01:14:10.000
in the inboxes.

01:14:11.000 --> 01:14:12.000
Important documents

01:14:13.000 --> 01:14:14.000
are often freely circulated

01:14:15.000 --> 01:14:16.000
on corporate networks,

01:14:17.000 --> 01:14:18.000
sometimes even in several copies.

01:14:19.000 --> 01:14:20.000
Your cooperation with colleagues

01:14:21.000 --> 01:14:22.000
can be more fruitful

01:14:23.000 --> 01:14:24.000
and the company's activities

01:14:25.000 --> 01:14:26.000
more successful

01:14:27.000 --> 01:14:28.000
if you use one of the network

01:14:29.000 --> 01:14:30.000
means of group work,

01:14:31.000 --> 01:14:32.000
which provide the opportunity

01:14:33.000 --> 01:14:34.000
to access information

01:14:35.000 --> 01:14:36.000
from any point in the world

01:14:37.000 --> 01:14:38.000
where there is an Internet access.

01:14:39.000 --> 01:14:40.000
For example,

01:14:41.000 --> 01:14:42.000
the development of Russian programmers

01:14:43.000 --> 01:14:44.000
and the operating system of the Motiv company

01:14:45.000 --> 01:14:46.000
allow you to participate in the life of your company

01:14:47.000 --> 01:14:48.000
by being in any point of the globe.

01:14:49.000 --> 01:14:50.000
It allows you to control

01:14:51.000 --> 01:14:52.000
the rising and descending

01:14:53.000 --> 01:14:54.000
horizontal information streams,

01:14:55.000 --> 01:14:56.000
to group information

01:14:57.000 --> 01:14:58.000
according to the characteristic

01:14:59.000 --> 01:15:00.000
convenient for the user,

01:15:01.000 --> 01:15:02.000
to automatically generate

01:15:03.000 --> 01:15:04.000
the information

01:15:05.000 --> 01:15:06.000
about the activity of the employees.

01:15:07.000 --> 01:15:08.000
All information about the course of the project,

01:15:09.000 --> 01:15:10.000
the tasks and assignments

01:15:11.000 --> 01:15:12.000
is stored in the database

01:15:13.000 --> 01:15:14.000
and is available at any time

01:15:15.000 --> 01:15:16.000
for work or acquaintance.

01:15:17.000 --> 01:15:18.000
The Motiv system

01:15:19.000 --> 01:15:20.000
allows you to work

01:15:21.000 --> 01:15:22.000
on common projects

01:15:23.000 --> 01:15:24.000
of partners, clients, and agents,

01:15:25.000 --> 01:15:26.000
creating a single information space

01:15:27.000 --> 01:15:28.000
between the participants

01:15:29.000 --> 01:15:30.000
of the communication process.

01:15:31.000 --> 01:15:32.000
There are many questions

01:15:33.000 --> 01:15:34.000
about the role of communication

01:15:35.000 --> 01:15:36.000
in the context of modern organizations.

01:15:37.000 --> 01:15:38.000
The interest in studying

01:15:39.000 --> 01:15:40.000
the female and male communication styles

01:15:41.000 --> 01:15:42.000
is not diminished.

01:15:43.000 --> 01:15:44.000
It is believed that men and women

01:15:45.000 --> 01:15:46.000
are taught and socialized

01:15:47.000 --> 01:15:48.000
in different ways,

01:15:49.000 --> 01:15:50.000
as a result of which

01:15:51.000 --> 01:15:52.000
they often experience difficulties

01:15:53.000 --> 01:15:54.000
in communicating with each other.

01:15:55.000 --> 01:15:56.000
Women in communication

01:15:57.000 --> 01:15:58.000
are focused on building relationships,

01:15:59.000 --> 01:16:00.000
while men try to

01:16:00.000 --> 01:16:01.000
surround them with individuals

01:16:02.000 --> 01:16:03.000
whose communication style

01:16:04.000 --> 01:16:05.000
is suitable for their own.

01:16:06.000 --> 01:16:07.000
The conclusion is that

01:16:08.000 --> 01:16:09.000
in the process of communication

01:16:10.000 --> 01:16:11.000
either women or men

01:16:12.000 --> 01:16:13.000
will dominate

01:16:14.000 --> 01:16:15.000
depending on who

01:16:16.000 --> 01:16:17.000
will be in the majority

01:16:18.000 --> 01:16:19.000
in a particular situation.

01:16:20.000 --> 01:16:21.000
Do women have better

01:16:22.000 --> 01:16:23.000
communication skills

01:16:24.000 --> 01:16:25.000
compared to men?

01:16:26.000 --> 01:16:27.000
The survey showed

01:16:28.000 --> 01:16:29.000
that in terms of communication skills,

01:16:30.000 --> 01:16:31.000
the women have a higher ability

01:16:32.000 --> 01:16:33.000
to find and meet,

01:16:34.000 --> 01:16:35.000
to give an assessment,

01:16:36.000 --> 01:16:37.000
and to delegate powers to others.

01:16:38.000 --> 01:16:39.000
The leadership evaluates

01:16:40.000 --> 01:16:41.000
women managers

01:16:42.000 --> 01:16:43.000
higher than their male colleagues.

01:16:44.000 --> 01:16:45.000
The subordinates also evaluated

01:16:46.000 --> 01:16:47.000
these abilities in women managers

01:16:48.000 --> 01:16:49.000
higher than in men.

01:16:50.000 --> 01:16:51.000
These results can be explained

01:16:52.000 --> 01:16:53.000
by the fact that early socialization

01:16:54.000 --> 01:16:55.000
and education

01:16:56.000 --> 01:16:57.000
improve women's

01:16:58.000 --> 01:16:59.000
communication skills

01:17:00.000 --> 01:17:01.000
and, on the contrary,

01:17:02.000 --> 01:17:03.000
men can socialize in such a way

01:17:04.000 --> 01:17:05.000
that it inevitably creates

01:17:06.000 --> 01:17:07.000
communication problems,

01:17:08.000 --> 01:17:09.000
aggression and spirit of rivalry.

01:17:10.000 --> 01:17:11.000
Taking this opportunity into account,

01:17:12.000 --> 01:17:13.000
it is very important to avoid

01:17:14.000 --> 01:17:15.000
gender stereotypes

01:17:16.000 --> 01:17:17.000
and focus your attention

01:17:18.000 --> 01:17:19.000
on the exclusively important question

01:17:20.000 --> 01:17:21.000
of how to maximize

01:17:22.000 --> 01:17:23.000
the effectiveness of communication

01:17:24.000 --> 01:17:25.000
in organizations.

01:17:26.000 --> 01:17:27.000
Today, many contradictions

01:17:28.000 --> 01:17:29.000
in organizational communications

01:17:30.000 --> 01:17:31.000
are being raised.

01:17:32.000 --> 01:17:33.000
One example is the control

01:17:34.000 --> 01:17:35.000
by employers

01:17:36.000 --> 01:17:37.000
over e-mails

01:17:38.000 --> 01:17:39.000
that employees send

01:17:40.000 --> 01:17:41.000
from their workplace.

01:17:42.000 --> 01:17:43.000
The study conducted

01:17:44.000 --> 01:17:45.000
by the American Association of Management

01:17:46.000 --> 01:17:47.000
found that the electronic control

01:17:48.000 --> 01:17:49.000
over the employee's activity

01:17:50.000 --> 01:17:51.000
increases by 45% per year.

01:17:52.000 --> 01:17:53.000
You may be surprised

01:17:54.000 --> 01:17:55.000
that most often

01:17:56.000 --> 01:17:57.000
bosses monitor the phone numbers

01:17:57.000 --> 01:17:58.000
of the employees

01:17:59.000 --> 01:18:00.000
and how long

01:18:01.000 --> 01:18:02.000
they talk on the phone.

01:18:03.000 --> 01:18:04.000
Then they monitor e-mails

01:18:05.000 --> 01:18:06.000
27% of all cases,

01:18:07.000 --> 01:18:08.000
computer files 21%

01:18:09.000 --> 01:18:10.000
and the content

01:18:11.000 --> 01:18:12.000
of phone conversations.

01:18:13.000 --> 01:18:14.000
The question of keeping secrets

01:18:15.000 --> 01:18:16.000
remains controversial

01:18:17.000 --> 01:18:18.000
because the continuous development

01:18:19.000 --> 01:18:20.000
of communication technologies

01:18:21.000 --> 01:18:22.000
makes it easier for employers

01:18:23.000 --> 01:18:24.000
to introduce electronic monitoring

01:18:24.000 --> 01:18:25.000
over how employees perform

01:18:26.000 --> 01:18:27.000
their work

01:18:28.000 --> 01:18:29.000
and carry out their communications.

01:18:30.000 --> 01:18:31.000
Our society is fighting

01:18:32.000 --> 01:18:33.000
for political correctness

01:18:34.000 --> 01:18:35.000
of communication at work.

01:18:36.000 --> 01:18:37.000
The working dictionary is changing

01:18:38.000 --> 01:18:39.000
and people are thinking more

01:18:40.000 --> 01:18:41.000
about not offending

01:18:42.000 --> 01:18:43.000
another person or a group of people.

01:18:44.000 --> 01:18:45.000
Today we use such terms

01:18:46.000 --> 01:18:47.000
as people with physical disabilities

01:18:48.000 --> 01:18:49.000
or people of older age.

01:18:50.000 --> 01:18:51.000
Not so long ago

01:18:52.000 --> 01:18:53.000
these groups of people

01:18:54.000 --> 01:18:55.000
were called differently

01:18:56.000 --> 01:18:57.000
and their names

01:18:58.000 --> 01:18:59.000
may change in the future.

01:19:00.000 --> 01:19:01.000
Organizations even organize

01:19:02.000 --> 01:19:03.000
special trainings

01:19:04.000 --> 01:19:05.000
for their employees

01:19:06.000 --> 01:19:07.000
to help them eliminate

01:19:08.000 --> 01:19:09.000
all shades of intolerance

01:19:10.000 --> 01:19:11.000
or inattention from the communication process.

01:19:12.000 --> 01:19:13.000
Open communication

01:19:14.000 --> 01:19:15.000
involves the exchange of information

01:19:16.000 --> 01:19:17.000
of all types

01:19:18.000 --> 01:19:19.000
between all structural

01:19:20.000 --> 01:19:21.000
divisions of the organization

01:19:21.000 --> 01:19:22.000
and hierarchical levels.

01:19:23.000 --> 01:19:24.000
Many companies

01:19:25.000 --> 01:19:26.000
open their financial documents

01:19:27.000 --> 01:19:28.000
and make them available

01:19:29.000 --> 01:19:30.000
to all levels of employees

01:19:31.000 --> 01:19:32.000
so that employees understand

01:19:33.000 --> 01:19:34.000
how and why the company

01:19:35.000 --> 01:19:36.000
works as it does.

01:19:37.000 --> 01:19:38.000
Open communication

01:19:39.000 --> 01:19:40.000
contradicts the traditional

01:19:41.000 --> 01:19:42.000
downward trend

01:19:43.000 --> 01:19:44.000
when the management

01:19:45.000 --> 01:19:46.000
sends the subordinates

01:19:47.000 --> 01:19:48.000
incomplete information.

01:19:49.000 --> 01:19:50.000
Getting rid of the usual

01:19:51.000 --> 01:19:52.000
and functional divisions

01:19:53.000 --> 01:19:54.000
of these potential

01:19:55.000 --> 01:19:56.000
communication barriers

01:19:57.000 --> 01:19:58.000
the organization gets the opportunity

01:19:59.000 --> 01:20:00.000
to use the ideas

01:20:01.000 --> 01:20:02.000
of all its employees.

01:20:03.000 --> 01:20:04.000
When the idea is circulated

01:20:05.000 --> 01:20:06.000
only in a narrow circle of managers

01:20:07.000 --> 01:20:08.000
there is no effective training

01:20:09.000 --> 01:20:10.000
or changes in the organization.

01:20:11.000 --> 01:20:12.000
There is no formation

01:20:13.000 --> 01:20:14.000
of a network of relationships

01:20:15.000 --> 01:20:16.000
thanks to which companies

01:20:17.000 --> 01:20:18.000
thrive in modern conditions.

01:20:19.000 --> 01:20:20.000
Attracting more people

01:20:21.000 --> 01:20:22.000
and a wider range of opinions

01:20:23.000 --> 01:20:24.000
is beneficial for organizational communication.

01:20:25.000 --> 01:20:26.000
In addition,

01:20:27.000 --> 01:20:28.000
open communication

01:20:29.000 --> 01:20:30.000
contributes to the appearance

01:20:31.000 --> 01:20:32.000
of trust and commitment

01:20:33.000 --> 01:20:34.000
to common goals.

01:20:35.000 --> 01:20:36.000
This is extremely important

01:20:37.000 --> 01:20:38.000
for organizations whose activities

01:20:39.000 --> 01:20:40.000
are associated with cooperation

01:20:41.000 --> 01:20:42.000
and knowledge exchange.

01:20:43.000 --> 01:20:44.000
Dialogue is a group

01:20:45.000 --> 01:20:46.000
communication process

01:20:47.000 --> 01:20:48.000
whose participants form

01:20:49.000 --> 01:20:50.000
a content stream of information

01:20:51.000 --> 01:20:52.000
and share their worldview.

01:20:53.000 --> 01:20:54.000
Initially,

01:20:55.000 --> 01:20:56.000
the participants of the dialogue

01:20:57.000 --> 01:20:58.000
can provide a complete

01:20:59.000 --> 01:21:00.000
opposite to each other,

01:21:01.000 --> 01:21:02.000
but through open discussion

01:21:03.000 --> 01:21:04.000
they find common ideals,

01:21:05.000 --> 01:21:06.000
common themes,

01:21:07.000 --> 01:21:08.000
common goals.

01:21:09.000 --> 01:21:10.000
It is easiest to describe

01:21:11.000 --> 01:21:12.000
the concept of dialogue

01:21:13.000 --> 01:21:14.000
by comparing it with a discussion.

01:21:15.000 --> 01:21:16.000
The differences between the two

01:21:17.000 --> 01:21:18.000
are presented on slide 31.

01:21:19.000 --> 01:21:20.000
The task of the discussion

01:21:21.000 --> 01:21:22.000
is to express

01:21:23.000 --> 01:21:24.000
one's point of view

01:21:25.000 --> 01:21:26.000
and convince others to accept it.

01:21:27.000 --> 01:21:28.000
The rule of the discussion

01:21:29.000 --> 01:21:30.000
and its logic

01:21:31.000 --> 01:21:32.000
is to break the resistance

01:21:33.000 --> 01:21:34.000
of the opposing side.

01:21:35.000 --> 01:21:36.000
In dialogue, on the contrary,

01:21:37.000 --> 01:21:38.000
the participants want

01:21:39.000 --> 01:21:40.000
to express their opinion

01:21:41.000 --> 01:21:42.000
and offer to speak

01:21:43.000 --> 01:21:44.000
on the other side

01:21:45.000 --> 01:21:46.000
on this topic.

01:21:47.000 --> 01:21:48.000
This allows to achieve

01:21:49.000 --> 01:21:50.000
a more complete understanding

01:21:51.000 --> 01:21:52.000
of the new ideas.

01:21:53.000 --> 01:21:54.000
The goal of dialogue

01:21:55.000 --> 01:21:56.000
is to understand each other's point of view

01:21:57.000 --> 01:21:58.000
and find points of contact.

01:21:59.000 --> 01:22:00.000
Both forms of communication

01:22:01.000 --> 01:22:02.000
and discussion and dialogue

01:22:03.000 --> 01:22:04.000
can lead to changes,

01:22:05.000 --> 01:22:06.000
but the result of the discussion

01:22:07.000 --> 01:22:08.000
is limited by the frameworks

01:22:09.000 --> 01:22:10.000
of the discussed topic,

01:22:11.000 --> 01:22:12.000
and the result of the dialogue

01:22:13.000 --> 01:22:14.000
is characterized by unity of opinions,

01:22:15.000 --> 01:22:16.000
common content

01:22:17.000 --> 01:22:18.000
and change of worldview.

01:22:19.000 --> 01:22:20.000
As the more deep

01:22:21.000 --> 01:22:22.000
the decisions between the participants

01:22:23.000 --> 01:22:24.000
of the dialogue,

01:22:25.000 --> 01:22:26.000
the more trustful

01:22:27.000 --> 01:22:28.000
and closer relations develop,

01:22:29.000 --> 01:22:30.000
which naturally contributes

01:22:31.000 --> 01:22:32.000
to the quality of communication.

01:22:33.000 --> 01:22:34.000
And finally, the final section,

01:22:35.000 --> 01:22:36.000
which needs to be discussed

01:22:37.000 --> 01:22:38.000
in more detail,

01:22:39.000 --> 01:22:40.000
is feedback and training.

01:22:41.000 --> 01:22:42.000
Feedback to the subordinate

01:22:43.000 --> 01:22:44.000
is the voice of the reaction

01:22:45.000 --> 01:22:46.000
to certain of his actions,

01:22:47.000 --> 01:22:48.000
and this is necessary

01:22:49.000 --> 01:22:50.000
for several reasons.

01:22:51.000 --> 01:22:52.000
First,

01:22:53.000 --> 01:22:54.000
this is a simple expression of attention,

01:22:55.000 --> 01:22:56.000
which, as various studies show,

01:22:57.000 --> 01:22:58.000
often has a beneficial effect

01:22:59.000 --> 01:23:00.000
on the relationship

01:23:01.000 --> 01:23:02.000
between people working together.

01:23:03.000 --> 01:23:04.000
Secondly,

01:23:05.000 --> 01:23:06.000
timely feedback

01:23:07.000 --> 01:23:08.000
allows to perform preventive work

01:23:09.000 --> 01:23:10.000
on the employee's mistakes.

01:23:11.000 --> 01:23:12.000
Thirdly, feedback

01:23:13.000 --> 01:23:14.000
has a motivating function.

01:23:15.000 --> 01:23:16.000
It allows the employee

01:23:17.000 --> 01:23:18.000
to find out what is expected of him

01:23:19.000 --> 01:23:20.000
and what are the criteria for assessment

01:23:21.000 --> 01:23:22.000
of his work.

01:23:23.000 --> 01:23:24.000
And most importantly,

01:23:25.000 --> 01:23:26.000
feedback allows to achieve

01:23:27.000 --> 01:23:28.000
the desired results from the employee.

01:23:29.000 --> 01:23:30.000
Feedback shows the employee

01:23:31.000 --> 01:23:32.000
how his work is evaluated.

01:23:33.000 --> 01:23:34.000
Therefore, as feedback,

01:23:35.000 --> 01:23:36.000
various instruments of stimulation

01:23:37.000 --> 01:23:38.000
such as indirect assessment tools

01:23:39.000 --> 01:23:40.000
can be considered.

01:23:41.000 --> 01:23:42.000
Such indirect tools include

01:23:43.000 --> 01:23:44.000
gratitude or reproach,

01:23:45.000 --> 01:23:46.000
reward or depression,

01:23:47.000 --> 01:23:48.000
increase or decrease

01:23:49.000 --> 01:23:50.000
of the employee's work,

01:23:51.000 --> 01:23:52.000
and service improvement.

01:23:53.000 --> 01:23:54.000
All these tools show

01:23:55.000 --> 01:23:56.000
whether the employee is evaluated

01:23:57.000 --> 01:23:58.000
well or badly.

01:23:59.000 --> 01:24:00.000
However, sometimes it is difficult

01:24:01.000 --> 01:24:02.000
for the employee to figure out

01:24:03.000 --> 01:24:04.000
what exactly he was encouraged

01:24:05.000 --> 01:24:06.000
or punished for.

01:24:07.000 --> 01:24:08.000
Therefore, feedback is effective

01:24:09.000 --> 01:24:10.000
only when the supervisor

01:24:11.000 --> 01:24:12.000
explains in detail

01:24:13.000 --> 01:24:14.000
what is good in his work

01:24:15.000 --> 01:24:16.000
and what is not very good.

01:24:17.000 --> 01:24:18.000
Therefore, the most effective

01:24:19.000 --> 01:24:20.000
feedback tool

01:24:21.000 --> 01:24:22.000
is the one provided by the employee

01:24:23.000 --> 01:24:24.000
when the employee not only

01:24:25.000 --> 01:24:26.000
learns about the assessment of his work,

01:24:27.000 --> 01:24:28.000
but also has the opportunity

01:24:29.000 --> 01:24:30.000
to ask questions

01:24:31.000 --> 01:24:32.000
and clarify incomprehensible points.

01:24:33.000 --> 01:24:34.000
There are various situations

01:24:35.000 --> 01:24:36.000
in the work life

01:24:37.000 --> 01:24:38.000
when the use of feedback

01:24:39.000 --> 01:24:40.000
is not only appropriate,

01:24:41.000 --> 01:24:42.000
but also necessary.

01:24:43.000 --> 01:24:44.000
Feedback is related to such types of feedback

01:24:45.000 --> 01:24:46.000
as assessment of the current

01:24:47.000 --> 01:24:48.000
activity of the employee,

01:24:49.000 --> 01:24:50.000
feedback on the employee's proposals,

01:24:51.000 --> 01:24:52.000
and feedback on the attitude

01:24:53.000 --> 01:24:54.000
of the employee

01:24:55.000 --> 01:24:56.000
to the company.

01:24:57.000 --> 01:24:58.000
The purpose of feedback

01:24:59.000 --> 01:25:00.000
on the current activity

01:25:01.000 --> 01:25:02.000
is to evaluate the employee's work,

01:25:03.000 --> 01:25:04.000
to show what is done well

01:25:05.000 --> 01:25:06.000
and what should be done in the future,

01:25:07.000 --> 01:25:08.000
to identify shortcomings

01:25:09.000 --> 01:25:10.000
and discuss ways to correct them.

01:25:11.000 --> 01:25:12.000
In addition, it is important

01:25:13.000 --> 01:25:14.000
to show the employee

01:25:15.000 --> 01:25:16.000
the importance of his work for the company,

01:25:17.000 --> 01:25:18.000
that is, to motivate him.

01:25:19.000 --> 01:25:20.000
The main rule is that

01:25:21.000 --> 01:25:22.000
feedback should be based on facts.

01:25:23.000 --> 01:25:24.000
Feedback should not be converted

01:25:25.000 --> 01:25:26.000
into a compliment or praise of the employee,

01:25:27.000 --> 01:25:28.000
that is,

01:25:29.000 --> 01:25:30.000
a compliment or a compliment

01:25:31.000 --> 01:25:32.000
of the employee's work.

01:25:33.000 --> 01:25:34.000
Feedback should ideally

01:25:35.000 --> 01:25:36.000
include highlighting

01:25:37.000 --> 01:25:38.000
the strengths of the employee's work,

01:25:39.000 --> 01:25:40.000
the behavior of the employee,

01:25:41.000 --> 01:25:42.000
and the weaknesses,

01:25:43.000 --> 01:25:44.000
that is, the places that require correction.

01:25:45.000 --> 01:25:46.000
Studies show

01:25:47.000 --> 01:25:48.000
that when analyzing the behavior

01:25:49.000 --> 01:25:50.000
of other people,

01:25:51.000 --> 01:25:52.000
we underestimate the influence

01:25:53.000 --> 01:25:54.000
of a person's nature

01:25:55.000 --> 01:25:56.000
and his personal abilities,

01:25:57.000 --> 01:25:58.000
and underestimate the influence

01:25:59.000 --> 01:26:00.000
of specific circumstances

01:26:01.000 --> 01:26:02.000
that affect

01:26:03.000 --> 01:26:04.000
a particular activity.

01:26:05.000 --> 01:26:06.000
For example,

01:26:07.000 --> 01:26:08.000
the reason for the employee's

01:26:09.000 --> 01:26:10.000
non-productive work

01:26:11.000 --> 01:26:12.000
is most likely due to the lack

01:26:13.000 --> 01:26:14.000
of personal abilities of the employee,

01:26:15.000 --> 01:26:16.000
not due to the situation

01:26:17.000 --> 01:26:18.000
at his workplace.

01:26:19.000 --> 01:26:20.000
This phenomenon is called

01:26:21.000 --> 01:26:22.000
a non-productive work.

01:26:23.000 --> 01:26:24.000
That is why it is very important

01:26:25.000 --> 01:26:26.000
to evaluate the employee,

01:26:27.000 --> 01:26:28.000
to talk to him,

01:26:29.000 --> 01:26:30.000
to clarify the situation

01:26:31.000 --> 01:26:32.000
in which he was

01:26:33.000 --> 01:26:34.000
and what influenced

01:26:35.000 --> 01:26:36.000
the result they presented.

01:26:37.000 --> 01:26:38.000
This approach will help

01:26:39.000 --> 01:26:40.000
to avoid mistakes

01:26:41.000 --> 01:26:42.000
when evaluating the employee's work

01:26:43.000 --> 01:26:44.000
and be objective.

01:26:45.000 --> 01:26:46.000
Feedback on the employee's proposals

01:26:47.000 --> 01:26:48.000
is intended to support the initiative,

01:26:49.000 --> 01:26:50.000
to increase motivation,

01:26:51.000 --> 01:26:52.000
and to promote the employee's work.

01:26:53.000 --> 01:26:54.000
If you are collecting the employee's proposals,

01:26:55.000 --> 01:26:56.000
you need to give feedback

01:26:57.000 --> 01:26:58.000
on all of them

01:26:59.000 --> 01:27:00.000
and take any action

01:27:01.000 --> 01:27:02.000
to show the employees

01:27:03.000 --> 01:27:04.000
that the situation will change

01:27:05.000 --> 01:27:06.000
or explain why the proposal

01:27:07.000 --> 01:27:08.000
is not accepted

01:27:09.000 --> 01:27:10.000
and the situation does not change.

01:27:11.000 --> 01:27:12.000
Conversations with feedback

01:27:13.000 --> 01:27:14.000
are made as the proposals

01:27:15.000 --> 01:27:16.000
are received from the employees.

01:27:17.000 --> 01:27:18.000
When preparing for such a conversation,

01:27:19.000 --> 01:27:20.000
the supervisor

01:27:21.000 --> 01:27:22.000
should study the employee's proposal,

01:27:23.000 --> 01:27:24.000
the written document

01:27:25.000 --> 01:27:26.000
or the conversation that took place,

01:27:27.000 --> 01:27:28.000
assess its relevance

01:27:29.000 --> 01:27:30.000
or novelty in the first approach,

01:27:31.000 --> 01:27:32.000
its timing,

01:27:33.000 --> 01:27:34.000
its necessity,

01:27:35.000 --> 01:27:36.000
make a decision

01:27:37.000 --> 01:27:38.000
and prepare arguments

01:27:39.000 --> 01:27:40.000
for refusal or vice versa,

01:27:41.000 --> 01:27:42.000
give the employee the approval

01:27:43.000 --> 01:27:44.000
and determine what further work is required.

01:27:45.000 --> 01:27:46.000
If the employee himself

01:27:47.000 --> 01:27:48.000
does not say something,

01:27:49.000 --> 01:27:50.000
then you need to ask the guiding questions.

01:27:51.000 --> 01:27:52.000
It is important that the employee

01:27:53.000 --> 01:27:54.000
speaks out all the above rules himself.

01:27:55.000 --> 01:27:56.000
Then he will be more realistic

01:27:57.000 --> 01:27:58.000
and critical

01:27:59.000 --> 01:28:00.000
about his proposal.

01:28:01.000 --> 01:28:02.000
Feedback on the employee's proposals

01:28:03.000 --> 01:28:04.000
should be presented as follows.

01:28:05.000 --> 01:28:06.000
First, what is interesting,

01:28:07.000 --> 01:28:08.000
what did the employee come up with

01:28:09.000 --> 01:28:10.000
and what is interesting

01:28:11.000 --> 01:28:12.000
the employee proposed.

01:28:13.000 --> 01:28:14.000
Second,

01:28:15.000 --> 01:28:16.000
what and where can be improved.

01:28:17.000 --> 01:28:18.000
Third,

01:28:18.000 --> 01:28:19.000
set the points of relevance,

01:28:20.000 --> 01:28:21.000
feasibility,

01:28:22.000 --> 01:28:23.000
adequacy of the proposed proposals.

01:28:24.000 --> 01:28:25.000
The fourth step

01:28:26.000 --> 01:28:27.000
is to make a general verdict

01:28:28.000 --> 01:28:29.000
whether it is accepted or not,

01:28:30.000 --> 01:28:31.000
whether it is accepted now

01:28:32.000 --> 01:28:33.000
or after a certain period of time.

01:28:34.000 --> 01:28:35.000
And the last step

01:28:36.000 --> 01:28:37.000
is to agree on the following actions

01:28:38.000 --> 01:28:39.000
that the employee should take

01:28:40.000 --> 01:28:41.000
in connection with his proposal.

01:28:42.000 --> 01:28:43.000
Feedback on the employee's plans

01:28:44.000 --> 01:28:45.000
is provided by the supervisor

01:28:45.000 --> 01:28:46.000
with such a periodicity

01:28:47.000 --> 01:28:48.000
that the plans themselves are prepared.

01:28:49.000 --> 01:28:50.000
Weekly plans,

01:28:51.000 --> 01:28:52.000
for example,

01:28:53.000 --> 01:28:54.000
for sales managers

01:28:55.000 --> 01:28:56.000
are better discussed every week

01:28:57.000 --> 01:28:58.000
for 5 or 10 minutes

01:28:59.000 --> 01:29:00.000
to control the motivation

01:29:01.000 --> 01:29:02.000
of prioritization.

01:29:03.000 --> 01:29:04.000
And monthly plans

01:29:05.000 --> 01:29:06.000
are discussed every month.

01:29:07.000 --> 01:29:08.000
The structure of the meeting

01:29:09.000 --> 01:29:10.000
on the discussion and approval of the plan

01:29:11.000 --> 01:29:12.000
may have different consequences.

01:29:12.000 --> 01:29:13.000
In the first case,

01:29:14.000 --> 01:29:15.000
if everything is not in line with the plan,

01:29:16.000 --> 01:29:17.000
the employee needs to be informed

01:29:18.000 --> 01:29:19.000
and if he has questions

01:29:20.000 --> 01:29:21.000
or needs to discuss something important,

01:29:22.000 --> 01:29:23.000
he needs to be helped.

01:29:24.000 --> 01:29:25.000
If the provided plan

01:29:26.000 --> 01:29:27.000
requires adjustments,

01:29:28.000 --> 01:29:29.000
the supervisor must decide

01:29:30.000 --> 01:29:31.000
what is in line with the plan

01:29:32.000 --> 01:29:33.000
and can be left,

01:29:34.000 --> 01:29:35.000
what is not in line with the plan

01:29:36.000 --> 01:29:37.000
and needs to be changed.

01:29:38.000 --> 01:29:39.000
And the supervisor

01:29:40.000 --> 01:29:41.000
must decide

01:29:42.000 --> 01:29:43.000
what needs to be improved.

01:29:44.000 --> 01:29:45.000
Then the supervisor

01:29:46.000 --> 01:29:47.000
must initiate a discussion

01:29:48.000 --> 01:29:49.000
on the issues

01:29:50.000 --> 01:29:51.000
that the employee has difficulties with

01:29:52.000 --> 01:29:53.000
or give information sources,

01:29:54.000 --> 01:29:55.000
give the employee a certain course of thought

01:29:56.000 --> 01:29:57.000
and finally agree on the terms

01:29:58.000 --> 01:29:59.000
of the provision of the revised plan.

01:30:00.000 --> 01:30:01.000
Feedback on the employee's reports

01:30:02.000 --> 01:30:03.000
The minimum that can be done

01:30:04.000 --> 01:30:05.000
is to inform the employee

01:30:06.000 --> 01:30:07.000
that the report was successfully accepted

01:30:08.000 --> 01:30:09.000
and note the most important

01:30:09.000 --> 01:30:10.000
merits and achievements of the employee.

01:30:11.000 --> 01:30:12.000
If the report requires

01:30:13.000 --> 01:30:14.000
some kind of adjustment,

01:30:15.000 --> 01:30:16.000
feedback on the employee's report

01:30:17.000 --> 01:30:18.000
can be given

01:30:19.000 --> 01:30:20.000
according to the following scheme.

01:30:21.000 --> 01:30:22.000
The first thing to do

01:30:23.000 --> 01:30:24.000
is that the supervisor

01:30:25.000 --> 01:30:26.000
must tell the employee

01:30:27.000 --> 01:30:28.000
what he is satisfied with

01:30:29.000 --> 01:30:30.000
in the work done during the reporting period,

01:30:31.000 --> 01:30:32.000
what was done well.

01:30:33.000 --> 01:30:34.000
Then the supervisor

01:30:35.000 --> 01:30:36.000
tells the employee

01:30:37.000 --> 01:30:38.000
what he is not satisfied with

01:30:39.000 --> 01:30:40.000
in the work done during the reporting period,

01:30:41.000 --> 01:30:42.000
what were the goals,

01:30:43.000 --> 01:30:44.000
what indicators were not achieved,

01:30:45.000 --> 01:30:46.000
in which tasks the priorities were set incorrectly,

01:30:47.000 --> 01:30:48.000
where the deadlines were broken,

01:30:49.000 --> 01:30:50.000
where the quality of the work was not satisfactory,

01:30:51.000 --> 01:30:52.000
and so on.

01:30:53.000 --> 01:30:54.000
The supervisor must also discuss

01:30:55.000 --> 01:30:56.000
with the employee

01:30:57.000 --> 01:30:58.000
the reason why he did not complete

01:30:59.000 --> 01:31:00.000
a particular task,

01:31:01.000 --> 01:31:02.000
what helps and what prevents

01:31:03.000 --> 01:31:04.000
the employee from solving the tasks set.

01:31:05.000 --> 01:31:06.000
How will he fix the situation?

01:31:07.000 --> 01:31:08.000
How to achieve the goals set?

01:31:09.000 --> 01:31:10.000
And the last thing

01:31:11.000 --> 01:31:12.000
is that the supervisor sets priorities

01:31:13.000 --> 01:31:14.000
in solving the tasks

01:31:15.000 --> 01:31:16.000
and mistakes of the employee.

01:31:17.000 --> 01:31:18.000
After providing the primary feedback

01:31:19.000 --> 01:31:20.000
on the supervisor's plans and reports,

01:31:21.000 --> 01:31:22.000
the employee must take

01:31:23.000 --> 01:31:24.000
a few more steps.

01:31:25.000 --> 01:31:26.000
The first thing is that the employee

01:31:27.000 --> 01:31:28.000
corrects or complements the plan or report

01:31:29.000 --> 01:31:30.000
taking into account the feedback from the supervisor.

01:31:31.000 --> 01:31:32.000
The second thing is that the supervisor

01:31:33.000 --> 01:31:34.000
studies the corrected documents.

01:31:35.000 --> 01:31:36.000
And the third thing is that the supervisor

01:31:37.000 --> 01:31:38.000
provides the final feedback

01:31:39.000 --> 01:31:40.000
on the attitude of the employee

01:31:41.000 --> 01:31:42.000
to what is happening in the company,

01:31:43.000 --> 01:31:44.000
on changes and innovations.

01:31:45.000 --> 01:31:46.000
Its goal is to avoid

01:31:47.000 --> 01:31:48.000
the misunderstanding of the staff

01:31:49.000 --> 01:31:50.000
set by the tasks, strategies

01:31:51.000 --> 01:31:52.000
and corporate values of the company.

01:31:53.000 --> 01:31:54.000
Usually, in order to introduce

01:31:55.000 --> 01:31:56.000
changes in the company,

01:31:57.000 --> 01:31:58.000
the employees are informed.

01:31:59.000 --> 01:32:00.000
That is, they say,

01:32:01.000 --> 01:32:02.000
for example,

01:32:03.000 --> 01:32:04.000
we decided to live in a new way.

01:32:05.000 --> 01:32:06.000
In order to introduce changes,

01:32:07.000 --> 01:32:08.000
the employees are informed

01:32:09.000 --> 01:32:10.000
and the company is informed.

01:32:11.000 --> 01:32:12.000
The most important thing

01:32:13.000 --> 01:32:14.000
is to ask the employees

01:32:15.000 --> 01:32:16.000
what they think about it,

01:32:17.000 --> 01:32:18.000
what are their concerns and objections.

01:32:19.000 --> 01:32:20.000
For these purposes,

01:32:21.000 --> 01:32:22.000
the survey is used,

01:32:23.000 --> 01:32:24.000
the method of box of proposals,

01:32:25.000 --> 01:32:26.000
personal conversations with the employee.

01:32:27.000 --> 01:32:28.000
As in the case of the employee's proposals,

01:32:29.000 --> 01:32:30.000
in no case can the employees

01:32:31.000 --> 01:32:32.000
be left without attention

01:32:33.000 --> 01:32:34.000
and concerns.

01:32:35.000 --> 01:32:36.000
Thus, the feedback of the employees

01:32:37.000 --> 01:32:38.000
should be contained in themselves.

01:32:39.000 --> 01:32:40.000
The first is the connection to the situation.

01:32:41.000 --> 01:32:42.000
That is, I understand

01:32:43.000 --> 01:32:44.000
that the upcoming changes

01:32:45.000 --> 01:32:46.000
will be quite difficult for us.

01:32:47.000 --> 01:32:48.000
This will bring a lot of new things

01:32:49.000 --> 01:32:50.000
to our activity.

01:32:51.000 --> 01:32:52.000
The second is the praise of the employee

01:32:53.000 --> 01:32:54.000
for certain concerns.

01:32:55.000 --> 01:32:56.000
It is very good that you noticed

01:32:57.000 --> 01:32:58.000
that in this situation

01:32:59.000 --> 01:33:00.000
certain aspects of our activity

01:33:01.000 --> 01:33:02.000
will change

01:33:03.000 --> 01:33:04.000
and we will have to do something.

01:33:05.000 --> 01:33:06.000
And finally, the last thing

01:33:07.000 --> 01:33:08.000
is the dissemination of myths.

01:33:09.000 --> 01:33:10.000
We should not answer

01:33:11.000 --> 01:33:12.000
the objections of the well-known leaders.

01:33:13.000 --> 01:33:14.000
After all, as you know,

01:33:15.000 --> 01:33:16.000
the root of all objections

01:33:17.000 --> 01:33:18.000
is the lack of information.

01:33:19.000 --> 01:33:20.000
That is, we need to continue

01:33:21.000 --> 01:33:22.000
this example

01:33:23.000 --> 01:33:24.000
by answering the objections

01:33:25.000 --> 01:33:26.000
that have come from employees.

01:33:27.000 --> 01:33:28.000
And in conclusion,

01:33:29.000 --> 01:33:30.000
let's add several rules

01:33:31.000 --> 01:33:32.000
to the principles of feedback

01:33:33.000 --> 01:33:34.000
that we have already discussed today.

01:33:35.000 --> 01:33:36.000
The first is that there should be feedback.

01:33:37.000 --> 01:33:38.000
It is not worth hoping

01:33:39.000 --> 01:33:40.000
that the employee will simply

01:33:41.000 --> 01:33:42.000
take into account the opinion of the leader

01:33:43.000 --> 01:33:44.000
or the significant silence

01:33:45.000 --> 01:33:46.000
that is required of him.

01:33:47.000 --> 01:33:48.000
The second is that feedback

01:33:49.000 --> 01:33:50.000
should be timely.

01:33:51.000 --> 01:33:52.000
It is not worth discussing the situation

01:33:53.000 --> 01:33:54.000
that happened a year ago.

01:33:55.000 --> 01:33:56.000
Even when providing

01:33:57.000 --> 01:33:58.000
negative feedback,

01:33:59.000 --> 01:34:00.000
you need to find something

01:34:01.000 --> 01:34:02.000
to praise the employee for.

01:34:03.000 --> 01:34:04.000
And you need to start

01:34:05.000 --> 01:34:06.000
with the assessment of what is good

01:34:07.000 --> 01:34:08.000
in his work.

01:34:09.000 --> 01:34:10.000
And you need to prepare

01:34:11.000 --> 01:34:12.000
for feedback.

01:34:13.000 --> 01:34:14.000
You should not expect

01:34:15.000 --> 01:34:16.000
that everything will change

01:34:17.000 --> 01:34:18.000
immediately after feedback.

01:34:19.000 --> 01:34:20.000
Unfortunately, feedback

01:34:21.000 --> 01:34:22.000
does not work like a magic wand.

01:34:23.000 --> 01:34:24.000
Change is a long and difficult process.

01:34:25.000 --> 01:34:26.000
Sometimes you need to repeat

01:34:27.000 --> 01:34:28.000
the same thing many times.

01:34:29.000 --> 01:34:30.000
After all, the habit of doing something

01:34:31.000 --> 01:34:32.000
in a certain way

01:34:33.000 --> 01:34:34.000
only goes away over time

01:34:35.000 --> 01:34:36.000
and with the correct reinforcement

01:34:37.000 --> 01:34:38.000
of the desired result.

01:34:39.000 --> 01:34:40.000
And this is one of the most powerful

01:34:41.000 --> 01:34:42.000
tools of staff management.

01:34:43.000 --> 01:34:44.000
If feedback is organized

01:34:45.000 --> 01:34:46.000
correctly and systematically,

01:34:47.000 --> 01:34:48.000
it allows you to achieve

01:34:49.000 --> 01:34:50.000
a positive attitude to tasks,

01:34:51.000 --> 01:34:53.000
a positive attitude to work tasks,

01:34:54.000 --> 01:34:55.000
to comments on his address,

01:34:56.000 --> 01:34:58.000
to understanding and acceptance of criticism,

01:34:59.000 --> 01:35:00.000
as well as the readiness

01:35:01.000 --> 01:35:02.000
to correct the shortcomings.

01:35:03.000 --> 01:35:04.000
The employee is ready

01:35:05.000 --> 01:35:06.000
and striving to correct

01:35:07.000 --> 01:35:08.000
his shortcomings

01:35:09.000 --> 01:35:10.000
and to improve his performance.

01:35:11.000 --> 01:35:12.000
Is this employee

01:35:13.000 --> 01:35:14.000
not a dream of any manager?

01:35:15.000 --> 01:35:16.000
In conclusion,

01:35:17.000 --> 01:35:18.000
I would like to say

01:35:19.000 --> 01:35:20.000
that in the last survey

